Biography

2011 game-by-game statistics | 2010 game-by-game statistics | 2009 game-by-game statistics

2010: Played in nine game – starting six – before injury ended season.

2009: Made 56 starts, including 31 in leftfield and 21 in right…finished second on the team with 47 runs driven in, thanks in part to 14 multi-RBI games…hit .380 with runners in scoring position and .643 with the bases loaded…swiped eight bases on 10 attempts…went yard in third collegiate at bat (2/6)…had at least two hits and two RBI in each of his first four collegiate games, finishing the West Georgia series going 9-for-16 with nine RBI and two homers…drove in five vs. Missouri-St. Louis (3/28), with four coming on a grand slam...racked up 12 RBI in a four-game stretch (3/28-4/4)…went 4-for-5 with three runs scored vs. Wis.-Parkside (4/25)…knocked in three in the GLVC Tournament win over USI (5/9).

High School: Garnered five letters in baseball and basketball …garnered hit .393 with five homers and 13 stolen bases as a senior on the way to All-State First Team recognition from Hoosier Diamond newspaper…also picked up all-conference, all-county and Indianapolis Star All-East honors that season…one of a crop of three UIndy players from New Pal's class of 2008 (Lawley & Rusche).

Personal: Majoring in Mechanical Engineering…played for the travel team Indiana Mustangs last year…son of Tim and Beth…born 7/18/89.

No stats available for the current season.
